TY  - JOUR
T1  - Quoting Customer Lead Times
AU  - Duenyas, Izak
AU  - Hopp, Wallace J.
Y1  - 1995/01/01
PY  - 1995
DA  - 1995/01/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.41.1.43
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.41.1.43
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 43
EP  - 57
VL  - 41
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We consider the problem of quoting customer lead times in a manufacturing environment under a variety of modeling assumptions. First, we examine the case where capacity is infinite. For this case, we derive a closed-form expression for the optimal lead time quote. Second, we consider the case where capacity is finite and the firm processes jobs in first-come-first-served (FCFS) order. We prove the optimality of different forms of control limit policies for the situations where the lead time is dictated by the market and where firms are able to compete on the basis of lead time. Finally, we consider the case where the firm may choose to schedule jobs in other than FCFS order and give conditions under which the optimal due-date-quoting/order-scheduling policy will process jobs in earliest due date (EDD) order.
AB  - We consider the problem of quoting customer lead times in a manufacturing environment under a variety of modeling assumptions. First, we examine the case where capacity is infinite. For this case, we derive a closed-form expression for the optimal lead time quote. Second, we consider the case where capacity is finite and the firm processes jobs in first-come-first-served (FCFS) order. We prove the optimality of different forms of control limit policies for the situations where the lead time is dictated by the market and where firms are able to compete on the basis of lead time. Finally, we consider the case where the firm may choose to schedule jobs in other than FCFS order and give conditions under which the optimal due-date-quoting/order-scheduling policy will process jobs in earliest due date (EDD) order.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.41.1.43
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.41.1.43
Y2  - 2024/03/28
